Ukraine May Sell Foreign-Currency Domestic Debt, Kommersant Says

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-12-01T07:52:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/ukraine-may-sell-foreign-currency-domestic-debt-kommersant-says.html
Ukraine may offer domestic government
bonds denominated in foreign currency to finance its state
budget gap,  Kommersant-Ukraine  reported, citing unidentified
people in the central bank and the Cabinet.  The bonds will be offered to banks as well as corporate and
individual investors, according to the newspaper based in the
capital, Kiev. The government will discuss the proposal next
week, Kommersant said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  